                <exercise id="fs-id1169736610446" type="problems-exercises"><problem id="fs-id1169736610448">    <para id="import-auto-id1169737722621">A radar used to detect the presence of aircraft receives a pulse that has reflected off an object <m:math><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mn>6</m:mn><m:mi>×</m:mi><m:msup><m:mtext>10</m:mtext><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mo stretchy="false">−</m:mo><m:mn>5</m:mn></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:msup><m:mspace width="0.25em"/><m:mtext> s</m:mtext></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:math> after it was transmitted. What is the distance from the radar station to the reflecting object?</para></problem></exercise>
                <exercise id="fs-id1169737796139" type="problems-exercises"><problem id="fs-id1169738013476">    <para id="import-auto-id1169738036036">Some radar systems detect the size and shape of objects such as aircraft and geological terrain. Approximately what is the smallest observable detail utilizing 500-MHz radar?</para>
